title: Elon Musk shockingly reveals Democrats are prolonging the government shutdown to keep illegal votes
description: The US government shutdown is now heading into its 33rd day and both Democrats and Republicans alike are sick and tired of it.    And whilst each side is blaming each other for the chaos, Elon Musk revealed the REAL reason behind the drawn out shutdown on the Joe Rogan podcast and according to him, the blame lies with the Democrats.

title: Kevin Rudd remains a ‘problem’ in US-Australia alliance
description: Former White House chief of staff Mick Mulvaney claims US Ambassador Kevin Rudd is still a “problem” in the alliance between Australia and the United States.  “I still think Kevin Rudd has got a problem and again, Trump continues to mention that in passing,” Mr Mulvaney said.  “But the relationship, I think, with Albanese, it was always going to be better than it was … it got off on a very, very bad first couple of steps.  “Albanese sort of took a step for the better over the course of the last several weeks, and he’s to be commended for that.”

title: Donald Trump and Xi Jinping’s relationship remains ‘as strong as ever’
description: Former White House chief of staff Mick Mulvaney weighs in on the meeting between US President Donald Trump and Chinese President Xi Jinping, saying the relationship between the two leaders remains “as strong as ever”.  “It was a good meeting with President Xi in South Korea. It wasn’t a comprehensive victory, it wasn’t a huge trade agreement on all topics,” Mr Mulvaney said.  “But it did move the ball in the right direction, and the relationship between the two men seems to be as strong as it ever has been.”

title: Democrats and Republicans share ‘blame’ for US government shutdown
description: Former White House chief of staff Mick Mulvaney claims both sides of politics are to “blame” for the US government shutdown.  “Politically, both parties think they are winning,” Mr Mulvaney said.  “If you’re trying to keep happy your base, either on the far left or the far right, I think you can make the argument that both parties are winning.  “Those folks in the middle blame both parties fairly evenly and in any event, very, very few of anybody actually changes who they vote for based on a government shutdown.”

title: Level of ‘public revulsion’ over Andrew reaches ‘fever pitch’
description: The Daily Mirror Royal Editor Russell Myers claims the level of “public revulsion” over Andrew Mountbatten Windsor has reached “fever pitch”.  “Andrew thought that he was completely shielded from that; he thought the King would protect him,” he told Sky News Australia.  “Reports of Fergie certainly asking for somewhere else to live after she was stripped of her Duchess of York title; the public was not certainly happy with that.”

title: Trump claims he is letting Putin ‘fight it out’ with Ukraine
description: US President Donald Trump claims Russia and Ukraine are “fighting it out”.  “It’s been a tough war for Putin … it’s been tough for Ukraine,” President Trump said on Air Force One.  “Sometimes you have to let it just get fought out.  “I’ve settled eight wars; I thought that that would be easier than ones we have settled.”

title: Donald Trump stresses the ‘very bad’ Nigerian Christian killings
description: US President Donald Trump said there “could be “ US forces on the ground in Nigeria amid mass Christian slaughters.  “They’re killing record numbers of Christians in Nigeria,” President Trump said on Air Force One.  “We’re not going to allow that to happen.”

title: ‘It’s good to see’: JD Vance dresses up as his own viral meme for Halloween
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond discusses US Vice President JD Vance dressing up for Halloween as a popular meme of himself.  “It’s good to see,” Mr Bond said.  “These people aren’t all humourless.”

title: ‘If we don’t have tariffs, we don’t have national security’: Donald Trump
description: US President Donald Trump discusses the importance of tariffs on Air Force One, claiming “without tariffs our country would be in great jeopardy”.  “I think it’s the most important decision … in the history of our country,” President Trump said.  “Without tariffs, without being able to use tariffs freely, openly, and in every way, we really would suffer tremendously from a national security standpoint.  “If we don’t have tariffs, we don’t have national security, and the rest of the world would laugh at us.”

title: 'The devil is not going to win': UK train knifeman’s chilling comments revealed
description: A survivor of a mass stabbing incident in the United Kingdom has revealed the chilling words the suspect said as she begged for her life.  Dayna Arnold was one of the several passengers aboard a train bound for London before a madman began stabbing “anyone he could find”.  The horrific attack took place on Saturday evening, with up to 11 people stabbed by a 32-year-old Black British man, with two fighting for their lives.  Though the 32-year-old man and another 35-year-old man were arrested, the second suspect was reportedly released on Sunday.  Arnold revealed the deranged attacker told her “the devil is not going to win” during an interview with ‘The Sun’.

title: ‘Just nuts’: Keir Starmer under fire for ‘wasting taxpayers’ money’
description: Former Liberal senator Hollie Hughes has hit out at the UK government over a multi-million-dollar road being built through the Amazon and funded by the British taxpayers.  “This is just nuts,” she said.  “Waste of money, taxpayers’ money, hence why Keir Starmer will be gone before we know it.”

title: ‘The next step the King will have to look at’: Calls for Andrew to be cut from succession line
description: The Daily Mirror Royal Editor Russell Myers discusses calls for Andrew Mountbatten Windsor to be cut from the line of succession.  This comes after King Charles removed his younger brother’s princely title and residence at Royal Lodge over his ties to convicted paedophile Jeffrey Epstein.  “Perhaps this is the next step that the King will have to look at,” Mr Myers told Sky News Australia.

title: Fergie’s career now ‘in tatters’ due to her own alleged ties to Epstein
description: The Daily Mirror Royal Editor Russell Myers claims Sarah Ferguson’s career is “in tatters now” because of her own alleged ties to Jeffrey Epstein.  “Reports of Fergie certainly asking for somewhere else to live after she was stripped of her Duchess of York title; the public was not certainly happy with that,” he told Sky News Australia.  “You look at her career, and it’ll certainly be in tatters now because of her own relationship with Jeffrey Epstein.”

title: ‘We got three of them back’: Trump addresses hostage situation on Air Force One
description: US President Donald Trump has spoken about the remains of the three deceased hostages returning to their families.  “We got three hostages back,” President Trump said on Air Force One.  “It’s so sad, we’re talking about dead bodies.   “We’re very happy to have done it.  “We’re looking for the remainder of the bodies.”

title: Cold and showery weather expected for Melbourne Cup day
description: Sky News Weather Senior Meteorologist Rob Sharpe provides an analysis of the wet weather forecast for the Melbourne Cup.  “It’s looking like a wet day, but for the race itself, we may escape the rainfall,” Mr Sharpe said.  “Melbourne may be between those two bands of wet weather right in time for the 3pm race, so that will be interesting to see how the weather plays out.”
